sarnow laboratory home page peter sarnow research summaries publications lab members lab alumni contact links microrna links scientific links stanford links german word the godfather home we are interested in virus host interactions and the mechanisms of cellular and viral translation much of our work has focused on translation initiation via both viral and cellular internal ribosomal entry sites ires's more recently however we have begun to investigate how micrornas regulate gene expression in mammalian cells although our interests encompass a variety of fields some of the specific questions we are asking include what kinds of specialized translation exist in the cell how do micrornas work what are the biological roles of micrornas what is the role of mir 122 in the hepatitis c virus life cycle how do viruses usurp the host cell stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
